Block shares also jumped after <a href="https://www.theblock.co/post/182791/block-reports-14-7-million-net-loss-in-q3-1-76-billion-in-bitcoin-sales" data-v-f87c67ca="">earnings</a> Thursday revealed total net revenue of $4.52 billion in the third quarter, which beat the $4.49 billion estimate and was up 17% year-over-year. Earnings per share also trounced expectations, coming in at 42 cents versus the 23 cent estimate. <br data-v-f87c67ca="">
<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
Excluding bitcoin revenue — $1.76 billion— net revenue was $2.75 billion.&nbsp;The company reported&nbsp;a net loss of $14.7 million for the third quarter.&nbsp;
